    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Stool examination via light microscopy of stained smears or wet mounts\nStool culture\n[4]\nELISA targeted at serum antibodies to Blastocystis species\n[5]\nPCR\n[6]\nFecal leukocytes are usually absent",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "",
      "subsections": {
        "Asymptomatic": {
          "text": "Do not require therapy",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Symptomatic": {
          "text": "Alternative diagnoses should be considered and excluded (e.g. alternative pathogen, noninfectious cause of symptoms)\nInitiation of treatment in symptomatic patients is controversial\nBlastocystis species infection is often self-limiting and many mild cases will resolve quickly\nTreatment options:\nMetronidazole\n(750 mg TID for 5-10 days)\n[7]\nTinidazole\n(2 mg once)\nAlternatives include: paromomycin, nitazoxanide, and trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
